1
00:02:10,759 --> 00:02:12,160
I really didn't know.

2
00:02:13,600 --> 00:02:15,000
I was too sleepy then.

3
00:02:15,040 --> 00:02:15,800
The fog was heavy,

4
00:02:15,800 --> 00:02:17,079
and there were no streetlights.

5
00:02:17,079 --> 00:02:17,720
I was just...

6
00:02:17,720 --> 00:02:19,640
I just got distracted for a moment,

7
00:02:19,640 --> 00:02:21,240
then I heard a bang.

8
00:02:21,400 --> 00:02:22,000
It just...

9
00:02:45,760 --> 00:02:46,800
I never expected

10
00:02:47,000 --> 00:02:47,530
there...

11
00:02:47,800 --> 00:02:48,329
there...

12
00:02:50,160 --> 00:02:51,480
to be a leg hanging.

13
00:02:54,600 --> 00:02:57,060
Son of a bitch, someone is trying to frame me.

14
00:03:04,040 --> 00:03:04,760
Captain Sun.

15
00:03:04,760 --> 00:03:07,040
I have a right lower limb dressed in women's clothing here.

16
00:03:07,040 --> 00:03:08,440
Based on the epiphyseal closure

17
00:03:08,440 --> 00:03:10,040
and initial observation of the skin condition,

18
00:03:10,040 --> 00:03:11,840
the victim is highly likely female.

19
00:03:11,840 --> 00:03:14,400
The estimated age is between 20 and 35.

20
00:03:14,960 --> 00:03:16,090
Crushed this badly.

21
00:03:16,640 --> 00:03:17,720
What about the other parts?

22
00:03:17,720 --> 00:03:18,579
Still looking.

23
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:20,440
The body is severely mutilated.

24
00:03:20,440 --> 00:03:22,700
Some parts are scattered over there too.

25
00:03:40,320 --> 00:03:41,050
Have a smoke.

26
00:03:41,400 --> 00:03:42,480
Next time, remember to

27
00:03:42,480 --> 00:03:43,280
stand upwind.

28
00:03:44,680 --> 00:03:45,920
You won't smell the corpse,

29
00:03:45,920 --> 00:03:46,960
but you'll smell

30
00:03:47,440 --> 00:03:48,640
how cowardly you are.

31
00:03:51,760 --> 00:03:52,960
Did you find the head?

32
00:03:54,120 --> 00:03:55,079
Not yet.

33
00:03:56,920 --> 00:03:57,680
Initially,

34
00:03:57,840 --> 00:03:59,640
the victim's neck muscles are torn,

35
00:03:59,640 --> 00:04:01,600
and the cervical spine has a scissor-like fracture,

36
00:04:01,600 --> 00:04:03,120
which matches the characteristics of a high-speed impact

37
00:04:03,120 --> 00:04:04,560
causing decapitation.

38
00:04:05,160 --> 00:04:06,640
There's also an impact wound on the shoulder.

39
00:04:06,640 --> 00:04:07,480
The scattered tissues

40
00:04:07,480 --> 00:04:09,760
all show signs of abrasions and dragging.

41
00:04:09,760 --> 00:04:11,840
Judging from the stiffness of the limbs,

42
00:04:11,840 --> 00:04:12,880
the time of death

43
00:04:13,200 --> 00:04:14,520
is within 12 hours.

44
00:04:21,160 --> 00:04:21,680
Master,

45
00:04:21,959 --> 00:04:23,820
why is there someone lying there?

46
00:04:45,159 --> 00:04:46,000
Oh, my god.

47
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:49,400
Chief Zhao said you were coming back today.

48
00:04:49,400 --> 00:04:50,120
I thought

49
00:04:50,360 --> 00:04:51,360
you would go back to report for duty.

50
00:04:51,360 --> 00:04:54,090
I didn't expect you to come straight to the scene.

51
00:05:12,840 --> 00:05:13,400
Sir,

52
00:05:13,440 --> 00:05:14,400
who is this?

53
00:05:15,040 --> 00:05:16,300
This is my old partner,

54
00:05:16,320 --> 00:05:16,880
Yan Mi.

55
00:05:18,960 --> 00:05:19,490
Brother,

56
00:05:20,160 --> 00:05:21,560
welcome back to the team.

57
00:05:23,360 --> 00:05:23,840
Yan.

58
00:05:24,120 --> 00:05:25,320
Let me introduce you.

59
00:05:25,320 --> 00:05:26,440
This is my new apprentice.

60
00:05:26,440 --> 00:05:27,440
His name is Jia Peng.

61
00:05:27,440 --> 00:05:28,770
He's very hardworking.

62
00:05:30,960 --> 00:05:31,600
Hello, Yan.

63
00:05:31,600 --> 00:05:32,320
I'm Jia.

64
00:05:45,120 --> 00:05:46,080
What are you doing, brother?

65
00:05:46,080 --> 00:05:46,810
Captain Sun,

66
00:05:47,720 --> 00:05:48,980
it seems our judgments

67
00:05:49,640 --> 00:05:50,680
are the same.

68
00:06:00,760 --> 00:06:02,220
This isn't a car accident.

69
00:06:03,680 --> 00:06:04,610
It's a body dump.

70
00:06:04,880 --> 00:06:05,880
A body dump?

71
00:06:06,520 --> 00:06:07,200
Why?

72
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:07,960
Master, didn't you just get here?

73
00:06:07,960 --> 00:06:08,920
How could you tell?

74
00:06:08,920 --> 00:06:09,360
First,

75
00:06:09,680 --> 00:06:12,010
we're nearly 40 kilometers from the city.

76
00:06:12,240 --> 00:06:13,520
Apart from the factories around here,

77
00:06:13,520 --> 00:06:15,320
there are no residential areas.

78
00:06:15,320 --> 00:06:16,600
It's deserted.

79
00:06:17,200 --> 00:06:18,660
Barely anyone comes here,

80
00:06:18,800 --> 00:06:21,130
except for large trucks smuggling goods.

81
00:06:21,360 --> 00:06:23,360
Judging from the condition of the body,

82
00:06:23,360 --> 00:06:24,960
the victim took good care of herself

83
00:06:24,960 --> 00:06:25,760
and her appearance.

84
00:06:25,760 --> 00:06:27,360
She wasn't a manual laborer.

85
00:06:27,760 --> 00:06:28,760
A woman like her,

86
00:06:29,040 --> 00:06:30,500
why would she appear here?

87
00:06:30,600 --> 00:06:32,159
And how did she end up here?

88
00:06:32,880 --> 00:06:33,480
Second,

89
00:06:37,560 --> 00:06:38,490
the bloodstains

90
00:06:39,240 --> 00:06:40,320
start from here.

91
00:06:40,440 --> 00:06:41,000
This is

92
00:06:41,040 --> 00:06:42,500
the first point of impact.

93
00:06:43,200 --> 00:06:44,460
It's a crushing point.

94
00:06:49,080 --> 00:06:50,320
If it were an impact,

95
00:06:50,640 --> 00:06:52,120
the body would fly out first.

96
00:06:52,120 --> 00:06:53,400
At the same time, there would be

97
00:06:53,400 --> 00:06:54,960
sprayed blood spatters around,

98
00:06:54,960 --> 00:06:56,520
then fall back to the ground,

99
00:06:56,520 --> 00:06:57,320
and roll over.

100
00:06:57,600 --> 00:06:58,240
However,

101
00:06:58,560 --> 00:07:01,080
the bloodstains left behind should have many patterns

102
00:07:01,080 --> 00:07:02,680
instead of being so uniform.

103
00:07:05,360 --> 00:07:07,490
But if someone familiar with this road

104
00:07:07,640 --> 00:07:09,400
deliberately dumped the body in the heavy fog

105
00:07:09,400 --> 00:07:11,930
to cover up the truth with a traffic accident,

106
00:07:12,080 --> 00:07:14,120
they would only leave crushing marks.

107
00:07:14,120 --> 00:07:15,080
Just like this.

108
00:07:17,320 --> 00:07:19,120
Although it covers a large area,

109
00:07:19,320 --> 00:07:21,480
there is almost no blood spatter.

110
00:07:21,840 --> 00:07:23,040
Let me sort this out.

111
00:07:23,400 --> 00:07:24,960
If they were dumping the body,

112
00:07:24,960 --> 00:07:25,800
the killer should have

113
00:07:25,800 --> 00:07:28,200
buried it in a remote place,

114
00:07:28,320 --> 00:07:29,640
instead of leaving it on the main road

115
00:07:29,640 --> 00:07:30,840
and drawing our attention.

116
00:07:30,840 --> 00:07:31,280
Wait.

117
00:07:31,800 --> 00:07:32,840
Why is that?

118
00:07:33,440 --> 00:07:35,500
That's what I'm trying to figure out.

119
00:07:35,600 --> 00:07:36,659
Is it a provocation

120
00:07:37,400 --> 00:07:38,240
or revenge?

121
00:08:26,240 --> 00:08:28,440
Have you determined the cause of death?

122
00:08:28,680 --> 00:08:31,120
The direct cause of death was excessive blood loss

123
00:08:31,120 --> 00:08:32,240
due to the complete decapitation.

124
00:08:32,240 --> 00:08:33,080
On the surface,

125
00:08:33,080 --> 00:08:34,120
the muscle, skin,

126
00:08:34,280 --> 00:08:35,320
and cervical spine sections

127
00:08:35,320 --> 00:08:36,919
are consistent with fatal high-speed impact.

128
00:08:36,919 --> 00:08:37,679
But in fact,

129
00:08:38,960 --> 00:08:40,890
it wasn't knocked off by an impact.

130
00:08:57,080 --> 00:08:59,000
In decapitation caused by a car accident,

131
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:01,280
the skin wound edges show radial tearing.

132
00:09:01,280 --> 00:09:03,040
The cervical spine cross-section shows multi-directional fractures

133
00:09:03,040 --> 00:09:04,320
and comminuted bursting.

134
00:09:04,320 --> 00:09:06,400
But the skin wound edges of this corpse

135
00:09:06,400 --> 00:09:07,920
show wavy tearing.

136
00:09:08,080 --> 00:09:09,040
There are unidirectional fractures

137
00:09:09,040 --> 00:09:10,700
and local compression marks.

138
00:09:11,040 --> 00:09:11,840
Furthermore,

139
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:13,080
we also detected

140
00:09:13,440 --> 00:09:15,200
trace metals in the wound.

141
00:09:15,920 --> 00:09:16,800
You mean

142
00:09:17,280 --> 00:09:20,210
her head was forcibly severed by some instrument...

143
00:09:20,680 --> 00:09:21,520
Cut with pliers.
